casebody.data:
UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Eduardo OROZCO-GOMEZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-51103

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 21, 2011. Joseph H. Gay, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, San Antonio, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Victor Manuel Serrano, Esq., El Paso, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before BENAVIDES, DENNIS, and SOUTHWICK, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Eduardo Orozco-Gomez has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir.2011). Orozco-Gomez has not filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s brief and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein. We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue *707for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cm. R. 47.5.4.
